<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 16 at 2:56AM CDT until April 16 at 10:00AM CDT by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 345 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHERN ADAIR AND SOUTHEASTERN CHEROKEE COUNTIES...
At 255 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles west of
Cookson, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations in or near the path include...
Stilwell...                       Cookson...
Adair State Park...               Baron...
Cherokee Landing State Park...    Maryetta...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
